SUMMARY:Free Class: Plumerias
LOCATION:4620 N. 22nd St. Tampa 33610 Tampa \, FL 33610 United States
DESCRIPTION:Overview: Tampa Family Health Centers (TFHC) hosts an interact
 ive class about plumerias. In this class\, Michael Masucci from the UFIFAS
  Extension Hillsborough County will talk about how to grow these easy\, be
 autiful plants. Bring plumeria cuttings for the plant swap! Visit our Well
 Fed table from 11:00 AM - 12:00 PM and taste samples of easy and delicious
  recipes. Registration: This is a free class. TFHC will provide the materi
 als\, but registration is required. Please note: Call or email Nicole Pins
 on\, npinsonhcnetwork.org or 813-459-3831\, TFHC Garden Manager\, with que
 stions. Space is limited to 50 participants. Event Location: The class beg
 ins at 9:30 AM. We will be located in the Employee Breakroom. We have a wa
 ter cooler and snack machine. Feel free to bring a beverage or your refill
 able water bottle. Partners: This event is brought to you through a partne
 rship with Tampa Family Health Centers\, Direct Relief\, Baxter Foundation
 \, UFIFAS Extension Hillsborough County\, and WellFed. \n\nPermalink: http
 s://www.tampa.gov/node/191066
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/191066
