SUMMARY:Heat is On- Staying Safe as Temperatures Rise
LOCATION:University of Tampa Vaughn Center 200 UT Poe Parkway 9th Floor Co
 nference Center Tampa \, FL 33606 United States
DESCRIPTION:Summer is upon us. We are seeing all kinds of weather extremes
  across the country as temperatures climb. Heat is an increasing factor wh
 ich puts our health at risk. Join us on Saturday\, June 13\, 2-4 pm to lea
 rn about why this is happening and what you can do to stay safe. Hear from
  News Channel 8s Chief Meteorologist and Climate Specialist\, Jeff Berarde
 lli. Known as the Weather Professor\, Jeff aims to educate the Tampa Bay c
 ommunity about our changing climate and how that impacts our home\, health
 \, and the World around us. We will also hear from experts in public healt
 h about what you can do to protect yourself as the heat rises. Sign up to 
 be part of this hot topic: REGISTER (https:www.mobilize.uscleoinstituteeve
 nt956393) Parking available: West Parking Garage Sponsors: WFLA News Chann
 el 8. City of Tampa\, USF College Of Public Health- Activist Lab\, AARP\, 
 Enterprising Latinas\, the University of Tampa\, genCLEO and The CLEO Inst
 itute \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/190851
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/190851
END:VEVENT
